        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"519727\">@Alice Ryhl</span> <br>\nI observe this strange behavior:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"k\">impl</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">kernel</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">Module</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">for</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">RustJobqueueTester</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">init</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">_module</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kp\">&amp;</span><span class=\"o\">'</span><span class=\"nb\">static</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">ThisModule</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nb\">Result</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"bp\">Self</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">pr_info</span><span class=\"o\">!</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"s\">\"Rust Jobqueue Tester (init)</span><span class=\"se\">\\n</span><span class=\"s\">\"</span><span class=\"p\">);</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">pr_info</span><span class=\"o\">!</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"s\">\"Am I built-in? {}</span><span class=\"se\">\\n</span><span class=\"s\">\"</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">!</span><span class=\"fm\">cfg!</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">MODULE</span><span class=\"p\">));</span>\n\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">mut</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">list</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">List</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">new</span><span class=\"p\">();</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">list</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">push_back</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">ListItem</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">new</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"mi\">14</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"o\">?</span><span class=\"p\">);</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">list</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">push_back</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">ListItem</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">new</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"mi\">12</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"o\">?</span><span class=\"p\">);</span>\n\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">mut</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">cursor</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">list</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">cursor_front</span><span class=\"p\">();</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"k\">while</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nb\">Some</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">elm</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">cursor</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">peek_next</span><span class=\"p\">()</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">_</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">elm</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">remove</span><span class=\"p\">();</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"n\">pr_info</span><span class=\"o\">!</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"s\">\"deleted one element.</span><span class=\"se\">\\n</span><span class=\"s\">\"</span><span class=\"p\">);</span>\n\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"n\">cursor</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">move_next</span><span class=\"p\">();</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"err\">…</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"w\">   </span><span class=\"mf\">67.806216</span><span class=\"p\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">rust_jobqueue_tester</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">Rust</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Jobqueue</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Tester</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">init</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"w\">   </span><span class=\"mf\">67.806222</span><span class=\"p\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">rust_jobqueue_tester</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">Am</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">I</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">built</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"k\">in</span><span class=\"o\">?</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kc\">false</span>\n<span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"w\">   </span><span class=\"mf\">67.806230</span><span class=\"p\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">rust_jobqueue_tester</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">deleted</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">one</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">element</span><span class=\"p\">.</span>\n<span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"w\">   </span><span class=\"mf\">67.806232</span><span class=\"p\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">rust_jobqueue_tester</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">Test</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">Test</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">submitting</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">two</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">jobs</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">without</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">dependencies</span><span class=\"p\">.</span>\n<span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"w\">   </span><span class=\"mf\">67.806239</span><span class=\"p\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">rust_kernel</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">Started</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">worker</span><span class=\"p\">.</span>\n<span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"w\">   </span><span class=\"mf\">67.806241</span><span class=\"p\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">rust_kernel</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">There</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">are</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">waiting</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">jobs</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Won</span><span class=\"o\">'</span><span class=\"na\">t</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">start</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">worker</span><span class=\"p\">.</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>That print occurs only once.<br>\nSame with my Jobqueue code, where a list with 2 elements experiences only 1 iteration with the shown cursor code.</p>\n<p>Is this intended behavior, am I misunderstanding the API?</p>",
        "id": 570598239,
        "sender_full_name": "Philipp Stanner",
        "timestamp": 1769615972
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>When you call <code>remove</code>, you shouldn't call <code>move_next</code> again, otherwise you're skipping over an element</p>",
        "id": 570605551,
        "sender_full_name": "Gary Guo",
        "timestamp": 1769617742
    },
    {
        "content": "<blockquote>\n<p>A cursor always rests between two elements in the list. This means that a cursor has a previous and next element, but no current element. It also means that it’s possible to have a cursor into an empty list.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p><a href=\"https://rust.docs.kernel.org/kernel/list/struct.Cursor.html\">https://rust.docs.kernel.org/kernel/list/struct.Cursor.html</a></p>",
        "id": 570614431,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1769619796
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>You may think of the List cursor as like the text cursor from when you write text. What you're doing is like pressing &lt;DELETE&gt;&lt;RIGHT ARROW&gt;, which will go from <code>A|BCD</code> -&gt; <code>A|CD</code> -&gt; <code>AC|D</code></p>",
        "id": 570619461,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1769621061
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Hm. We probably want to pretty up the documentation a bit. Another team member of mine also didn't get it <span aria-label=\"face with spiral eyes\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f635-200d-1f4ab\" role=\"img\" title=\"face with spiral eyes\">:face_with_spiral_eyes:</span></p>",
        "id": 570720868,
        "sender_full_name": "Philipp Stanner",
        "timestamp": 1769671866
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Is a list for-each iterator with modifyable entries conceivable in Rust that does not rely on the user manually moving the cursor?</p>\n<p>It's quite easy to accidentally built buggy loops, like infinite loops, with the current API</p>",
        "id": 570722850,
        "sender_full_name": "Philipp Stanner",
        "timestamp": 1769672656
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>You may be able to write an iterator over <code>CursorPeek</code>, or something similar.</p>",
        "id": 570729468,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1769674867
    }
